refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
arrayget_loaded_extensions boolzend_extensionsfalse
This function returns the names of all the modules compiled and loaded in the PHP interpreter.

&reftitle.parameters;
zend_extensions
Only return Zend extensions, if not then regular extensions, like mysqli is listed. Defaults to &false; (return regular extensions).

&reftitle.changelog;







     &Version;
     &Description;





     5.2.4

      The optional zend_extensions parameter was added

&reftitle.examples;
get_loaded_extensions Example
<?php print_r(get_loaded_extensions()); ?>
&example.outputs.similar;
Array ( [0] => xml [1] => wddx [2] => standard [3] => session [4] => posix [5] => pgsql [6] => pcre [7] => gd [8] => ftp [9] => db [10] => calendar [11] => bcmath )
